.dataset property 

In JavaScript, .dataset is a property that allows you to access custom data attributes on HTML elements. These custom data attributes are prefixed with data- in the HTML code and can be used to store information that you want to associate with the element.
<div id="myElement" data-rating="5"></div>
var element = document.getElementById('myElement');
var rating = element.dataset.rating;
console.log(rating); // Output: 5



